                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d484">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00Sonora/817: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Nogales</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Damm</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nogales, Ariz</hi>
                        </placeName>., <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-26T12:00:00-06:00"
                            >April 26, 1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From Guaymas:</p>
                <p>“Urgent for Department. April 26, 10 a.m. Eaton<note n="61" xml:id="d484fn61"
                        >Vice Consul in charge at Ciudad Obregon.</note> reports Federals bomb
                    dropped through roof of his office yesterday without injury to him but some
                    material damage. I have telegraphed to General Calles and requested that orders
                    be given to prevent repetition of the incident. Eaton also reports rebel retreat
                    under way with destination reported to be Guaymas. Present whereabouts
                    retreating rebels unknown due to the interruption of communications”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Damm</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
